## Output format

Write a SINGLE JSON object to `{output_path}`. Schema:

```json
{{
  "question_id": "{qid}",
  "question": "{question}",
  "lang": "{lang}",
  "regime": "A|B|C",
  "response": "<your full response, markdown body with all sections per RESPONSE_TEMPLATES>",
  "atoms_cited": ["[[{lang}/wiki/atom-stem-1]]", "[[{lang}/wiki/atom-stem-2]]"],
  "sources_cited": [
    {{"source_id": "VIDEO_ID", "url": "https://youtube.com/watch?v=VIDEO_ID&t=83", "locator": "01:23-01:47"}}
  ],
  "conflict_detected": {{"found": false, "severity": null, "atoms": []}},
  "proposed_contradictions": [],
  "self_assessment": {{
    "confidence": "high|medium|low",
    "completeness": 1,
    "accuracy": 1,
    "regime_chosen": "A|B|C",
    "word_count": 0
  }}
}}
```

`proposed_contradictions[]` follows CLAUDE.md §4.5.5 — emit an entry only when you detect a HIGH/MEDIUM conflict that is NOT yet documented in `meta/contradictions.md`.

Save the JSON to `{output_path}` and stop. No other output.
